snippet.textDisplay:
Yes, Coke Studio Pakistan was below par but you have to understand that CSP had raised the bar way way too high, which is why this season seems pale in comparison. And while Uzair and Bilal may be popcorn singers they did spring their share of surprises by having the likes of Chakwal Group, Bohemia, Qayaas to go with the in house band that is a class in itself. Also, as much as I hate to admit it, their sub par season would outweigh Coke Studio by some distance.

PS - I'm a music lover.

snippet.textDisplay:
Listen dude!
Uzair Jaswal and Bilal Khan, both are very much talented artists and Coke Studio isn't all about having serious music, it's about experimenting... It's not about having hard-to-understand lyrics, sometimes lyrics are easy-to-understand and that's perfectly alright... and this year's season was much much better than the previous two...
Hadiqa, Bilal Khan, Symt, Overload, Chakwal Group, Uzair Jaswal, Hamayoon Khan, Farid Ayaz & Abu Muhammad... All of them did a great job!
